The paper deals with the problem of computing Maximum Independent Set in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The algorithm presented in the paper is based on a dynamic programming approach that exploits the structure of graphs with bounded degree 3. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-areas of computer science, such as data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and graph theory (cs.GT).
